git clone https://github.com/LondheShubham153/django-notes-app.git

git checkout dev
cd django notes-app
build image :- docker build -t monudocker334/notes-app:latest .
push to dockerhub :- docker push monudocker334/notes-app:latest
docker rmi image ID
*******************************************************************************
Nginx
Install Nginx reverse proxy to make this application available

sudo apt-get update sudo apt install nginx

üîÅ Step 3: Configure Nginx as a Reverse Proxy
Create a new Nginx config file for your app:

sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/notes-app

Add the following configuration:

nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name your_domain_or_ip;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:8000;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}

Replace your_domain_or_ip with your actual domain name or public IP address.

Enable the site:
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/notes-app /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/

Test the configuration:
sudo nginx -t

Reload Nginx:
sudo systemctl reload nginx
********************************************************************************************
Create dir k8s and create namespace, deployment and service.yml
kubectl create namespace notes-app

nano deployment.yml

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: notes-app-deployment
  namespace: notes-app
  labels:
    app: notes-app
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: notes-app
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: notes-app
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: notes-app
        image: monudocker334/notes-app-k8s:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8000
nano service.yml

kind: Service
apiVersion: v1
metadata:
  name: notes-app-service
  namespace: notes-app

spec:
  selector:
    app: notes-app
  ports:
    - protocol: TCP
      port: 8000
      targetPort: 8000
  type: ClusterIP
    
kubectl apply -f .
Access notes app in ubuntu VM local : localhost:8000
kubectl delete -f .
*************************************************************************************************************
You can delete all the resources in the workshop namespace using this command:

kubectl delete all --all -n notes-app
This will delete:

All Pods
All Services
All Deployments
All ReplicaSets
Everything managed by kubectl get all
